More than 40 suspects were arrested for the deadly 2020 church attack but one of the opposing factions of the International Pentecost Holiness Church believes there's still no justice. JOHANNESBURG - More than 40 suspects were arrested for the deadly 2020 church attack but one of the opposing factions of the International Pentecost Holiness Church believes there's still no justice.
Gunmen stormed the multi-million rand church compound in Zuurbekom outside Johannesburg about a year and a half ago, leaving five bodies in their wake.
A long-term dispute over who should lead the church is said to be at the heart of this case.